{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f24b3c23-49a0-425d-b2b7-7059333d26d3","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use the **lifecycle mapping events** on `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents` in your `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n- Each platform has its own extension method (`AddAndroid`, `AddiOS`, `AddWindows`, etc.) with callbacks matching native events.\n- Use `#if` platform directives so the code compiles only for the target platform.\n- Other useful Android events: `OnResume`, `OnDestroy`, `OnCreate`.\n- Other useful iOS events: `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate`, `OnActivated`.\n\nSee the official docs: [.NET MAUI App Lifecycle](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/maui/fundamentals/app-lifecycle).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b1474f5a-119c-4c0c-b189-49a84355b093","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question, not a code task in the repository.","outputTokens":384,"requestId":"9BC8:21A8FE:61A05FE:6CCD768:69EC0E9F"},"id":"3a3122d0-26d8-4415-a2e7-4e4ca7e80c4f","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:45:27.757Z","parentId":"c4e0762e-4bd7-4ea3-8957-9ae7d4944217"}
